The day began with an enlightening session conducted by the RUET Astronomy and Science Society, taking participants on a journey through stars, science, and curiosity. The session inspired enthusiasm and deeper interest in astronomy by blending scientific concepts with engaging discussions. Following the session, participants resumed their three-day group initiatives, working closely with mentors to refine ideas and explore innovative approaches to cosmic themes. Collaboration, creativity, and problem-solving were evident as teams actively discussed concepts and brought their astronomical visions to life. The environment was filled with excitement, curiosity, and a shared passion for learning. Through hands-on engagement and mentorship, participants strengthened teamwork skills and scientific thinking. The day truly reflected curiosity in action, where learning met imagination, reinforcing the spirit of exploration and discovery that defined the overall camp experience.
